01:39:22,000 --> 01:39:37,000
Because her parents said they wanted the world to remember her as she was a bright child with hope and possibilities.

769
01:39:38,000 --> 01:39:42,000
And you know what that little girl was singing and her brother was playing?

770
01:39:42,000 --> 01:39:46,000
Night one, Mr. Note.

771
01:39:46,000 --> 01:39:53,000
Come, thou Almighty King. Help us, thy name, to sing.

772
01:39:53,000 --> 01:39:58,000
Father, all glorious, all over all victorious.

773
01:39:58,000 --> 01:40:06,000
Come and rank over us, ancient of days.

774
01:40:07,000 --> 01:40:26,000
If we were to take the heart, the lyrics of that song, we would see that in this nation that should reign supreme, a universal spirit and practice.

775
01:40:27,000 --> 01:40:47,000
That whether child is in violence, in new town, my town, or whatever town, we should show concern and show as great passion for all as we do for one.

776
01:40:47,000 --> 01:41:02,000
And I think that, though new town, maybe with the tipping point, we have the occasion now to deal with this culture of violence in America.

777
01:41:02,000 --> 01:41:14,000
I just got back from a meeting on Friday with the senior staff, the chief of staff, vice president Biden.

778
01:41:14,000 --> 01:41:26,000
With Franklin Graham and Richard Land of the Southern Baptist Convention, who was over the public policy and social justice commission of the Southern Baptist.

779
01:41:26,000 --> 01:41:29,000
That's the largest Protestant nomination in the nation.

780
01:41:29,000 --> 01:41:40,000
Out of that meeting, it was the agreement that we're going to call faith leaders together at the White House.

781
01:41:40,000 --> 01:41:49,000
Possibly around the time of the anniversary of the assassination of Dr. King, April 4th.

782
01:41:49,000 --> 01:42:09,000
Evangelicals from the White community, traditional civil rights leaders, Black faith leaders, people of all faith communities, to pledge our support for this president as he seeks to come up with sensible,

783
01:42:09,000 --> 01:42:19,000
measures to get us beyond this culture of violence.

784
01:42:19,000 --> 01:42:38,000
And already we agreed upon universal background checks, expansion of the mental health programs, addressing the issue of the exposure of children to this cultural violence that's in these video games.

785
01:42:38,000 --> 01:42:45,000
And many of these real violent movies that are coming out of Hollywood.

786
01:42:45,000 --> 01:42:48,000
So I think that's the beginning point.

787
01:42:48,000 --> 01:42:58,000
Even though we still have miles to go and more to do in promises to keep, to address the semi-automatic weapons.

788
01:42:58,000 --> 01:43:03,000
But I feel that we're on our way.

789
01:43:03,000 --> 01:43:15,000
Of course, we're ridiculous that we have 12,000 to 12,000 homicides a year in this country.

790
01:43:15,000 --> 01:43:21,000
And other countries, you know, 30, 40, maybe 50.

791
01:43:21,000 --> 01:43:24,000
We're violent culture.

792
